params.label: Type
params.description:
Type of item bank. One of the following:

  • Direct - items are declared directly on node
  • Table - items are read from data table
params.name: itemBankType

params.label: Order
params.description:
Order of items. One of the following:

  • Manual - will use sorted orderIndex column for order
  • Random - item order will be randomized
params.name: order

params.label: Can Go Back?
params.description: Should it be possible to go back to already answered items and change your response?
params.name: canGoBack

params.label: Test Time Limit
params.description: Total test time limit in seconds. 0 for no limit.
params.name: testTimeLimit

params.label: Item Time Limit
params.description: Time limit, in seconds, for each item. 0 for none.
params.name: itemTimeLimit

params.label: Sufficient Item Time Required
params.description: If checked your total test time left must be greater or equal to item time limit. Otherwise no further questions will be shown.
params.name: itemTimeFullRequired

params.label: Item Number Limit
params.description: Maximum number of items. 0 for no limit.
params.name: itemNumLimit

params.label: Response Bank
params.description: Response column mapping. Don't select any table if you do not wish to store responses in your data tables.
params.name: responseBank

params.label: Response required alert
params.description: Alert when no response is given.
params.name: responseRequiredAlert

steps.title: Modules
steps.description: Test modules. Each module is a separate test that can use specific input variables and must return specific return variables.

params.label: Next Item Selector Module
params.description:
Next item selector module. Needs to return:

  • nextItem - list, next item to show
  • nextItemIndex - numerical, index of next item to show
  • nextItemSafe - list, next item to show with all sensitive data fields removed
  • pastResponseSafe - list, past response for next item with all sensitive data fields removed
params.name: nextItemSelectorModule

params.label: Scoring Module
params.description:
Scoring module. Needs to return:

  • score - numerical, score for last response given
  • scores - vector, scores for all past responses
  • traitScores - list, keys are trait names and values are total scores for given trait
params.name: scoringModule

params.label: Response Processor Module
params.description:
Response processor module. Must return:

  • direction - numerical, positive for next item, negative for previous item
  • itemsAdministered - vector, contains all indices of already administered items
  • responseId - id of inserted response record to database
params.name: responseProcessorModule

params.label: Status Check Module
params.description:
Status check module. Checks whether test should continue or end. Must return:

  • .branch - string, shoul be continue if test should continue or stop if it should be stopped
params.name: statusCheckModule
